        "details": {
            "description": "<p>A clockwork bomb releases gouts of poisonous smoke. The smoke issues forth from a single nozzle attached to two tanks of pressurized poison</p>",
            "disable": "<p>Three DC 31 Thievery (expert) checks to @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Disable Device]{Disable a Device} to disable the latches that lock the nozzle in place, then one DC 35 Thievery (master) check to Disable a Device to turn off the nozzle; DCs decrease by 2 if Oggvurm is immobilized, paralyzed, unconscious, or dead</p>",
            "isComplex": true,
            "level": {
                "value": 11
            },
            "reset": "The trap issues smoke for 3 minutes before its tanks run dry. The tanks must be replaced before the bomb can be reactivated.",
            "routine": "<p>(1 action) On its turn, the bomb spews forth a smoky gout of airborne @Compendium[pf2e.equipment-srd.Blackfinger Blight]{Blackfinger Blight} poison. The cloud fills a 20-foot radius, or a 10-foot radius if only one tank remains intact. If the bomb is already in the center of a blackfinger blight cloud, the radius of that cloud increases by 20 feet (or 10 feet, if only one tank remains intact) instead.</p>"
